article.headline: Winthrop 65, Radford 55
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- James Shuler scored 18 points as Winthrop picked up its 11th consecutive win 65-55 over Radford Wednesday night. Shuler was the only scorer in double digits for the Eagles (20-5, 11-1 Big South Conference), but players came off the bench to contribute 23, led by Otis Daniels' nine. Olumuyiwa Popoola had 14 points for Radford (10-13, 5-7), which turned the ball over 19 times. Chris Oliver added 11 points. Winthrop led throughout, although neither team shot above 39 percent on the night.
